{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864029150,"sessionID":"ses_286418634ffea8pAZ41CVyQMqj","part":{"id":"prt_d79be9643001v66xEHfDMiDIF3","messageID":"msg_d79be885b001mOq6xRHigQ7j8A","sessionID":"ses_286418634ffea8pAZ41CVyQMqj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4891310d81354e8d99394d11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that enable users to interact with and monitor published AI agents.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack → build → publish → **invoke** → **status**. The `invoke` and `status` commands are the final two steps, enabling agent interaction and status monitoring.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Implement the `invoke` command that:\n16: 1. Loads workspace metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n17: 2. Parses and validates JSON payload\n18: 3. Parses custom HTTP headers\n19: 4. Resolves the agent endpoint from metadata\n20: 5. Sends HTTP POST request to the agent\n21: 6. Displays the response\n22: \n23: Implement the `status` command that:\n24: 1. Loads workspace metadata\n25: 2. Checks if agent is published\n26: 3. Queries the target provider for deployment status\n27: 4. Displays status in a Rich Table\n28: \n29: ### Value\n30: \n31: - **Direct Agent Interaction**: POST JSON payloads to invoke agents\n32: - **Flexible Headers**: Support custom HTTP headers for authentication\n33: - **Status Monitoring**: Real-time deployment status check\n34: - **Dual Provider Support**: Works with both AgentCube CRD and K8s deployments\n35: - **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## Scope\n40: \n41: ### In-Scope\n42: \n43: | Component | Path | Description |\n44: |-----------|------|-------------|\n45: | Invoke command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n46: | Invoke runtime | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Core invoke logic |\n47: | Status command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n48: | Status runtime | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Core status logic |\n49: | Metadata models | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | AgentMetadata |\n50: | Tests | `tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`, `tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Unit tests |\n51: \n52: ### CLI Interface\n53: \n54: #### invoke\n55: \n56: ```python\n57: def invoke(\n58:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n59:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n60:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n61:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n62:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n63: ) -> None:\n64: ```\n65: \n66: #### status\n67: \n68: ```python\n69: def status(\n70:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n71:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n72:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n73: ) -> None:\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### InvokeRuntime API\n77: \n78: ```python\n79: class InvokeRuntime:\n80:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n81:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: str, payload: str, header_list: Optional[List[str]], provider: str, verbose: bool) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n82:     def _resolve_endpoint(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: str) -> str: ...\n83:     async def _invoke_async(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], provider: str) -> Any: ...\n84:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n85:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### StatusRuntime API\n89: \n90: ```python\n91: class StatusRuntime:\n92:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n93:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: str, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n94:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n95:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### Out-of-Scope\n99: \n100: - Agent deployment (handled by publish command)\n101: - WebSocket connections for streaming\n102: - Long-running agent sessions\n103: - Interactive agent REPL\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Impact Analysis\n108: \n109: ### Dependencies\n110: \n111: | Dependency | Purpose |\n112: |------------|---------|\n113: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | Async HTTP client for agent invocation |\n114: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n115: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n116: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | Metadata serialization |\n117: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n118: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s status queries |\n119: \n120: ### Upstream\n121: \n122: - **cli-toolkit/design.md** — InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime class designs\n123: - **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Invoke and status command requirements and scenarios\n124: - **AR-020 (pack)** — Requires packed workspace with metadata\n125: - **AR-021 (build)** — Requires built Docker image\n126: - **AR-022 (publish)** — Requires published agent endpoint\n127: \n128: ### Downstream Consumers\n129: \n130: 1. **End users** — Fourth and fifth CLI commands in agent workflow\n131: 2. **CI/CD pipelines** — Automated testing and deployment verification\n132: 3. **Monitoring systems** — Status polling integration\n133: \n134: ### Risks\n135: \n136: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n137: |------|----------|------------|\n138: | Agent not published | High | Clear error message before HTTP request |\n139: | Invalid JSON payload | High | Validate JSON before sending request |\n140: | Invalid header format | Medium | Validate format (key:value) before request |\n141: | Network timeout | Medium | Configurable timeout, clear error message |\n142: | K8s cluster inaccessible | Medium | Error handling with fallback message |\n143: | Provider mismatch | Low | Validate provider matches published type |\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Alternatives Considered\n148: \n149: ### Option 1: Direct HTTP Calls (Selected)\n150: \n151: **Approach**: Use httpx AsyncClient for direct HTTP invocations.\n152: \n153: **Pros**:\n154: - Simple implementation\n155: - No additional dependencies\n156: - Async support for better performance\n157: - Works with any HTTP endpoint\n158: \n159: **Cons**:\n160: - No built-in retry logic\n161: - No connection pooling by default\n162: \n163: **Decision**: Selected — aligns with spec requirements and existing patterns.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ### Option 2: SDK-Based Invocation (Not Selected)\n168: \n169: **Approach**: Use Python SDK (AgentRuntimeClient) for invocations.\n170: \n171: **Pros**:\n172: - Higher-level abstraction\n173: - Built-in session management\n174: \n175: **Cons**:\n176: - Adds SDK dependency\n177: - Less flexible for custom headers\n178: - Endpoint rewriting not supported\n179: \n180: **Decision**: Not selected — spec requires direct HTTP with endpoint rewriting.\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## Implementation Plan\n185: \n186: ### Phase 1: InvokeRuntime Core\n187: - [x] Implement `_resolve_endpoint()` method\n188: - [x] Implement `_direct_http_invocation()` method\n189: - [x] Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` method\n190: - [x] Implement `invoke()` method with payload/header parsing\n191: \n192: ### Phase 2: StatusRuntime Core\n193: - [x] Implement `_get_k8s_status()` method\n194: - [x] Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status()` method\n195: - [x] Implement `get_status()` method\n196: \n197: ### Phase 3: CLI Integration (invoke)\n198: - [x] Add invoke command to main.py Typer app\n199: - [x] Implement Rich output for response display\n200: - [x] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n201: - [x] Handle invalid JSON payload validation\n202: - [x] Handle invalid header format validation\n203: \n204: ### Phase 4: CLI Integration (status)\n205: - [ ] Add status command to main.py Typer app\n206: - [ ] Implement Rich Table for status display\n207: - [ ] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n208: - [ ] Handle not_published status\n209: - [ ] Handle error status\n210: \n211: ### Phase 5: Testing\n212: - [ ] Unit tests for InvokeRuntime methods\n213: - [ ] Unit tests for StatusRuntime methods\n214: - [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n215: - [ ] Mock HTTP tests for invoke\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Acceptance Criteria\n220: \n221: ### Invoke Command\n222: \n223: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n224: |----|----------|-----------------|\n225: | AI-001 | Valid workspace, valid JSON payload | Agent invoked successfully, response displayed |\n226: | AI-002 | Invalid JSON payload | Error message, exit code 1 |\n227: | AI-003 | Invalid header format (no colon) | Error message, exit code 1 |\n228: | AI-004 | Valid custom headers | Headers included in request |\n229: | AI-005 | Agent not published | Error message, exit code 1 |\n230: | AI-006 | Session ID in metadata | X-Agentcube-Session-Id header added |\n231: | AI-007 | AgentCube provider endpoint rewriting | URL rewritten to /v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/ |\n232: | AI-008 | HTTP error response | Error message with status code |\n233: | AI-009 | Network timeout | Timeout error message |\n234: \n235: ### Status Command\n236: \n237: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n238: |----|----------|-----------------|\n239: | AS-001 | Published agent (agentcube) | AgentRuntime status displayed in table |\n240: | AS-002 | Published agent (k8s) | Deployment status displayed in table |\n241: | AS-003 | Agent not published | \"not_published\" status, exit code 1 |\n242: | AS-004 | Error retrieving status | \"error\" status with error message |\n243: | AS-005 | Custom namespace | Namespace shown in status |\n244: | AS-006 | AgentRuntime CR has status field | Display phase from status |\n245: | AS-007 | AgentRuntime CR has no status | Display \"created_no_status\" |\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Technical Design\n250: \n251: ### Invoke Flow\n252: \n253: ```\n254: invoke command\n255:     │\n256:     ├─→ Parse CLI options\n257:     │   ├─→ Validate JSON payload\n258:     │   └─→ Parse headers (key:value format)\n259:     │\n260:     ├─→ Load workspace metadata\n261:     │   └─→ Check agent_id or agent_endpoint exists\n262:     │\n263:     ├─→ Resolve endpoint\n264:     │   └─→ Use agent_endpoint if available\n265:     │   └─→ Construct from agent_id + namespace + port otherwise\n266:     │\n267:     ├─→ Add session header if session_id exists\n268:     │   └─→ X-Agentcube-Session-Id: {session_id}\n269:     │\n270:     ├─→ HTTP POST to endpoint\n271:     │   └─→ Content-Type: application/json\n272:     │   └─→ Body: {payload}\n273:     │\n274:     └─→ Display response (Rich output)\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### Status Flow\n278: \n279: ```\n280: status command\n281:     │\n282:     ├─→ Load workspace metadata\n283:     │\n284:     ├─→ Check if published (agent_id or agent_endpoint)\n285:     │   └─→ If not published: return \"not_published\"\n286:     │\n287:     ├─→ Query provider\n288:     │   ├─→ agentcube: _get_cr_k8s_status()\n289:     │   │   └─→ Query AgentRuntime CR\n290:     │   │   └─→ Return status.phase or \"created_no_status\"\n291:     │   └─→ k8s: _get_k8s_status()\n292:     │       └─→ Query Deployment status\n293:     │       └─→ Return pod status\n294:     │\n295:     ├─→ Display in Rich Table\n296:     │   ├─→ Agent Name\n297:     │   ├─→ Status\n298:     │   ├─→ Endpoint\n299:     │   └─→ Namespace\n300:     │\n301:     └─→ Exit code 1 if not_published or error\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ### Endpoint Resolution Logic\n305: \n306: ```python\n307: def _resolve_endpoint(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: str) -> str:\n308:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n309:     \n310:     # Use explicit endpoint if available\n311:     if metadata.agent_endpoint:\n312:         return metadata.agent_endpoint\n313:     \n314:     # Construct from agent_id\n315:     if metadata.agent_id:\n316:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n317:         return f\"http://{metadata.agent_id}.{namespace}.svc.cluster.local:{metadata.port}\"\n318:     \n319:     raise ValueError(\"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\")\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Header Parsing Logic\n323: \n324: ```python\n325: def _parse_headers(self, header_list: Optional[List[str]]) -> Dict[str, str]:\n326:     if not header_list:\n327:         return {}\n328:     \n329:     headers = {}\n330:     for header in header_list:\n331:         if \":\" not in header:\n332:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid header format: {header}. Expected key:value\")\n333:         key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n334:         headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n335:     \n336:     return headers\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ## Timeline Estimate\n342: \n343: | Phase | Effort |\n344: |-------|--------|\n345: | InvokeRuntime Core | 1-2 hours |\n346: | StatusRuntime Core | 1 hour |\n347: | CLI Integration (invoke) | 1-2 hours |\n348: | CLI Integration (status) | 1-2 hours |\n349: | Testing | 2-3 hours |\n350: | **Total** | **6-10 hours** |\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ## Existing Implementation Status\n355: \n356: The invoke and status commands have partial implementations:\n357: \n358: 1. **InvokeRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`): 234 lines, implements core invoke logic with async HTTP client\n359: 2. **StatusRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`): 143 lines, implements status retrieval for both providers\n360: \n361: ### Known Issues\n362: \n363: 1. **invoke_runtime.py line 62**: Bug - `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` assigns `response` only inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError`\n364: 2. **CLI integration**: Commands need to be added to `main.py` with proper Typer bindings\n365: 3. **Status output**: Needs Rich Table implementation in CLI\n366: 4. **Exit codes**: Status should exit with code 1 for not_published/error\n367: \n368: ### Gaps to Address\n369: \n370: 1. Fix UnboundLocalError bug in invoke_runtime.py\n371: 2. Add invoke command to main.py Typer app\n372: 3. Add status command to main.py Typer app\n373: 4. Implement Rich Table output for status\n374: 5. Implement proper exit codes for error conditions\n375: 6. Add session header support (X-Agentcube-Session-Id)\n\n(End of file - total 375 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that enable users to interact with and monitor published AI agents.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack → build → publish → **invoke** → **status**. The `invoke` and `status` commands are the final two steps, enabling agent interaction and status monitoring.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement the `invoke` command that:\n1. Loads workspace metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n2. Parses and validates JSON payload\n3. Parses custom HTTP headers\n4. Resolves the agent endpoint from metadata\n5. Sends HTTP POST request to the agent","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775864029117,"end":1775864029147}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864029152,"sessionID":"ses_286418634ffea8pAZ41CVyQMqj","part":{"id":"prt_d79be9953001Qvi0A0EsSNN3Uk","messageID":"msg_d79be885b001mOq6xRHigQ7j8A","sessionID":"ses_286418634ffea8pAZ41CVyQMqj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_35afbfc209444075adfc521c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/test_spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/test_spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube 测试用例规范 (TDD Specification)\n2: \n3: 要求 AI 在实现业务代码时，同步完成以下测试用例，作为实现完成度的判定标准。\n4: \n5: ## 1. 核心控制器测试 (Workload Manager)\n6: - **TestCase-WM-001**: 验证 Sandbox 创建接口。输入合法 `AgentRuntime` 定义，预期返回 `200 OK` 及 `sessionId`。\n7: - **TestCase-WM-002**: 验证 Sandbox 幂等性。相同 `name` 连续调用两次，预期返回相同 `sessionId`。\n8: - **TestCase-WM-003**: 验证非法输入拦截。输入缺失 `podTemplate` 的请求，预期返回 `400 Bad Request`。\n9: \n10: ## 2. 路由与会话测试 (Router)\n11: - **TestCase-RT-001**: 验证 Auth 拦截。未携带 Bearer Token 请求 `/v1/execute`，预期返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n12: - **TestCase-RT-002**: 验证会话路由。模拟 Redis 中存在会话，Router 成功将请求转发至后端（Mock 后端）。\n13: - **TestCase-RT-003**: 验证会话过期。模拟 Redis 中 Token 已失效，返回 `404 Not Found`。\n14: \n15: ## 3. 存储层测试 (Store)\n16: - **TestCase-ST-001**: Redis Set/Get 验证。成功存储并检索 `SessionInfo` 结构体。\n17: - **TestCase-ST-002**: 过期时间验证。验证 Key 携带正确的 TTL（默认 24h）。\n18: \n19: ## 4. 编码执行引擎测试 (PicoD)\n20: - **TestCase-PD-001**: Python 代码执行。发送 `print(\"hello\")`，预期 stdout 为 `hello\\n`，exitCode 为 0。\n21: - **TestCase-PD-002**: 错误处理。发送语法错误代码，预期 stderr 包含 `SyntaxError`。\n22: \n23: ## 5. Python SDK 测试\n24: - **TestCase-SDK-001**: 上下文管理器验证。使用 `with CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:` 确保结束时自动调用 `close()`。\n25: - **TestCase-SDK-002**: 异常映射。服务端返回 500 时，SDK 抛出自定义 `AgentCubeError` 而非原始 HTTP 错误。\n26: \n27: ## 实施要求\n28: - **Go 代码**：必须位于对应的 `*_test.go` 中，可通过 `go test ./...` 运行。\n29: - **Python 代码**：必须位于 `tests/` 目录或 `test_*.py` 文件中，可通过 `pytest` 运行。\n\n(End of file - total 29 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube 测试用例规范 (TDD Specification)\n\n要求 AI 在实现业务代码时，同步完成以下测试用例，作为实现完成度的判定标准。\n\n## 1. 核心控制器测试 (Workload Manager)\n- **TestCase-WM-001**: 验证 Sandbox 创建接口。输入合法 `AgentRuntime` 定义，预期返回 `200 OK` 及 `sessionId`。\n- **TestCase-WM-002**: 验证 Sandbox 幂等性。相同 `name` 连续调用两次，预期返回相同 `sessionId`。\n- **TestCase-WM-003**: 验证非法输入拦截。输入缺失 `podTemplate` 的请求，预期返回 `400 Bad Request`。\n\n## 2. 路由与会话测试 (Router)\n- **TestCase-RT-001**: 验证 Auth 拦截。未携带 Bearer Token 请求 `/v1/execute`，预期返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n- **TestCase-RT-002**: 验证会话路由。模拟 Redis 中存在会话，Router 成功将请求转发至后端（Mock 后端）。\n- **TestCase-RT-003**: 验证会话过期。模拟 Redis 中 Token 已失效，返回 `404 Not Found`。\n\n## 3. 存储层测试 (Store)\n- **TestCase-ST-001**: Redis Set/Get 验证。成功存储并检索 `SessionInfo` 结构体。\n- **TestCase-ST-002**: 过期时间验证。验证 Key 携带正确的 TTL（默认 24h）。\n\n## 4. 编码执行引擎测试 (PicoD)\n- **TestCase-PD-001**: Python 代码执行。发送 `print(\"hello\")`，预期 stdout 为 `hello\\n`，exitCode 为 0。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/test_spec.md","time":{"start":1775864029120,"end":1775864029150}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864029156,"sessionID":"ses_286418634ffea8pAZ41CVyQMqj","part":{"id":"prt_d79be9ccd001JoICRHwMLf730A","messageID":"msg_d79be885b001mOq6xRHigQ7j8A","sessionID":"ses_286418634ffea8pAZ41CVyQMqj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1f7ead738b5c4ce5bc69d660","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-020\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n25: \n26: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n31: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n32: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n33: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n38: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n39: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n40: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n45: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n46: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n51: - **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n57: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n63: \n64: The system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n69: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n71: - **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n76: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n78: - **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n83: - **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n85:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n86:   - `port`: `8080`\n87:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n88:   - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n93: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n95:   - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n96:   - `--language` overrides `language`\n97:   - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n98:   - `--port` overrides `port`\n99:   - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n100:   - `--description` overrides `description`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n105: \n106: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n111: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n113: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n118: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n120: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n125: - **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n127: - **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n132: \n133: The system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n138: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n139: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n144: - **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n145: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n150: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n156: \n157: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n162: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n163: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n168: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n174: - **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n180: \n181: The system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n186: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n187:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n188:   - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n189:   - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n190:   - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n191:   - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n192:   - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n193:   - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n194:   - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n195:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n200: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n201: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n202: - **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n207: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n208: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n209: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n214: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n215: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n216: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n221: \n222: The system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n225: \n226: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n227: - **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n228: - **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n233: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n234: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n239: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n240: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n245: \n246: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n251: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n252: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n253: - **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n258: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n260: - **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Acceptance Criteria\n265: \n266: - [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n267: - [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n268: - [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n269: - [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n270: - [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n271: - [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n272: - [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n273: - [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n274: - [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n275: - [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Architecture Notes\n280: \n281: ### Key Components\n282: \n283: | Component | Path | Description |\n284: |-----------|------|-------------|\n285: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n286: | PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n287: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n288: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n289: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n290: \n291: ### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n292: \n293: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n294: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n295: | agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n296: | language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n297: | entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n298: | port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n299: | build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n300: | description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n301: | requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n302: \n303: ### CLI Options Mapping\n304: \n305: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n306: |------------|----------------|------|\n307: | `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n308: | `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n309: | `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n310: | `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n311: | `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n312: | `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n313: | `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## References\n318: \n319: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n320: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n321: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n322: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n323: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n324: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864029122,"end":1775864029153}}}}
